Summary of ASX Announcement (C29 Metals)

Strategic Shift & Project Focus:
- Exit Kazakhstan: Termination of operations due to unresolved regulatory hurdles; surrender of Kazakh tenements in progress.
- Termination of HOA: Binding Heads of Agreement with Bask International terminated.
- Refocus on Mayfield Project (QLD):
- 3-year exploration license extension secured (expires March 2028).
- Geophysical anomalies (gravity/IP) correlate with copper/gold mineralization (e.g., 12m @ 1.55% Cu in drilling).
- Targets: Mylonite-hosted gold and ironstone-hosted Cu-Au systems.

Operational Highlights:
- Historic drilling at Mayfield includes:
- Clarries Prospect: 75m @ 0.21% Cu (intersected in 2023).
- Trekelano South: Proximity to past-producing mine (3.1Mt @ 2.1% Cu, 0.64g/t Au).

No new material exploration data (per ASX Listing Rule 5.23).

Critical Impact:
- Strategic pivot to Australian assets may alter valuation focus; exit from Kazakhstan reduces geopolitical risk but abandons potential resource upside.
- License extension and confirmed mineralization at Mayfield support near-term exploration upside.

Actionable Catalyst: Planned exploration at Mayfield (timeline undisclosed).

No capital raising, financials, or definitive timetable disclosed.

• Project Highlights:
  • Rover 1 Project: High-grade Iron Oxide Copper Gold (IOCG) deposit with critical minerals (gold, copper, cobalt, bismuth, magnetite).
  • Mineral Resources:
    • Total Resource: 5,581kt @ 1.76g/t Au, 1.49% Cu, 0.07% Co, 0.11% Bi, 23.20% Fe3O4.
    • Bismuth Resource: 5,900t (4,200t Indicated @ 0.11% Bi).
  • Production Targets (PFS):
    • Avg. annual production: 28,700oz Au, 6,900t Cu, 300t Co, 75,300t Fe3O4.
    • Life-of-mine: 252,300oz Au, 58,600t Cu.

  • Financials (2022 PFS, pre-tax):

    • NPV6.5%: A$451.5M | IRR: 45.9% | Payback: 31 months.
    • Avg. annual free cash flow: A$109.1M.

  • Catalysts:

  • Bankable Feasibility Study (BFS) underway for Rover 1.

  • Major Project Status awarded (ASX 18 Apr 2024), with land allocated at Middle Arm Sustainable Development Precinct (Darwin).

  • Market Context:

  • Bismuth price surge: Reported at US$55/lb (A$192,500/t) in March 2025; Rover 1 hosts one of few global resources.

  • Exploration: 100+ IOCG targets; Ambient Noise Tomography (ANT) surveys ongoing.

  • Capital Structure:

  • Cash (Mar 2025): A$4.8M.

  • Shares Outstanding: 300M | Market Cap: A$18.0M (@ A$0.06/share).

  • Key Risks: Funding, commodity price volatility, and execution of BFS/strategic partnerships.

No material trading or capital-raising actions announced. Focus remains on project advancement and resource valuation.

Summary of ASX Announcement (2 July 2025) – Marmota Limited (ASX: MEU)

  • Drilling Program Initiation: Maiden RC drilling program at Greenewood gold discovery (Gawler Gold project)
  • Scope: 127 planned RC holes, ~10,000m total drilling, average depth ~79m.

  • Timing: Commencing in ~5 days; permits secured.

  • Ownership & Context:

  • Greenewood held under Golden Moon JV (Marmota 90% via Half Moon); ministerial consent recently granted.
  • First drilling at Greenewood since 2018; total historical drilling: 8,245m (new program doubles RC holes).

  • Adjacent to flagship Aurora Tank deposit (~35km away); potential operational synergies.

  • Gold Market: Current gold price (~A$5,000/oz) tripled since 2018 (A$1,600/oz), enhancing project economics.
